args:
Once the fiends are slain, the concert begins!
After Cleo gives Siren a handmade costume
and wears a swimsuit in her role as a backup
dancer, the show is an utter smash! In the end,
Siren and Cleo conquer their fears and make
a host of treasured summer memories.
Goodness, what an exciting opening act!\nEr, that WAS an act...right?
All right, folks! Now that we've warmed\nup the stage for her, it's time to put\nyour hands together for...SIIIIIREN!
She should be ready any minute now,\nso raise your voices and let her know\nthat YOU'RE all ready, too!
Everyone is calling my name...\nThis is totally a dream.
This is no dream, Siren—and it is\nyour courage that made it real.
Er, Verica? Why are you wearing that?
Am I not your backup dancer?\nOr should I say...ONE of them?
Ohmigosh, Cleo, you look AMAZING!\nBut wait, don't you totally hate swimsuits?
I decided that I, too, desired change.
And that there is nothing shameful about\nwearing swimsuits—or having fun.
I had told myself that a prince's attendant\nneeded to refrain from such things.
But that was merely an excuse,\nand I knew that to be the case.
So rather than declaring I could not do\nsuch things, I swore to be more true to\nmyself—much like you are, in fact.
I want to stand on that stage with you\nin this outfit and make a summer memory\nI will never forget. So...will you have me?
Duh! Of COURSE I will, you dingus!\nNow let's get out there and make\nmemories until we drop!
Oh, and I have something for you...
I thought you might want a stage outfit for\nyour big moment.
I know what this performance means to\nyou, and I wanted to make something\nto recognize that.
Although it is perfectly all right if this\nparticular outfit is not your style.
Cleooooo! I looooove it!\nC'mere and hug me, girl!
Bwah! I wasn't really expecting a hug...
If you two are done here, we have an\nentire audience that is waiting.
Right! Lemme just get changed here...
Okay, we're totes good to go.\nLet's do this, ladies!
Woo hoo! Let's make some noooooise!
(This day has finally come.\nI'm...not alone anymore.)
(So many nights spent alone...\nSo many mornings crying...)
(But now I feel like I love everything,\nand it's all 'cause I met you guys.)
(Now it's my turn to make YOU happy.)
(I am going to put every drop of my\nemotion into my music and, like,\nblast it back out to everyone!)
(It's time to show 'em how\nmuch they mean to me!)
Hee hee! That was great... So happy... \nSoooo hungry... *sniff*
I'm good if ya laugh, cry, or eat,\nbut ya gotta pick one, yeah?
Nothing beats barbecue after a hard\nnight's work, right? Mmmmmmm...
Hmm. Cleo seems to be missing again.\nI'll see if I can find her.
Oh, hello. Do you need something,\n{player_name}.
I'm just looking for you, actually.\nEveryone's eating, and I thought\nyou'd want to come join us.
I am already full—or perhaps it is\nsimply my heart that is full.
Mind if I sit with you, then?
Well, it was a bit rough at times, but we\nmanaged to make that concert happen.\nWhat do you think? Did you enjoy it?
Of course. Although the dancing part\nwas difficult...and rather embarrassing.
Well, you looked like a natural up there.\nIt really was a new side of you!
Heh. A jest only, I assure you.\nIn truth, I even surprised myself\na bit with my boldness.
I've been finding all sorts of reasons to\navoid that sort of thing—claiming it was\nbecause I was an attendant and such.
I always get timid at events like this.\nIt's as if I am waiting for someone to\ntell me it is acceptable to enjoy myself.
But watching Siren made me realize\nhow wrong that mindset is.
What I really wanted was to join in on\nthe fun. That's what I've ALWAYS wanted.
If I had simply put on the flashy clothes\nand danced and sung and laughed,\nI would have all sorts of happy memories.
I don't want such regrets anymore.
Sounds like you've taken a bold step.\nI'm glad to hear it.
You're a serious person, Cleo, and maybe\nthat's what causes you to hesitate...
But whenever I see you smile, it makes\nme happier than you will ever know.
So I hope you'll keep pushing yourself\nlike you did tonight.
It's okay to enjoy yourself. Really.
Oh no, Your Majesty. I could never...
(＂There is nothing wrong with\nenjoying yourself, you know?＂)
(That's what His Majesty said to me\nthat day.)
(I finally remembered his words.\nHis vitally important words.)
Sorry, did I say something strange?
I enjoy every moment that I spend with\nyou all, and know I will continue to do so.
That's really great to hear, Cleo.\nShould we head back to the others, then?
We can walk together, if you want.
(I want to make many happy memories\nand keep them inside me forever.)
(Summer may be ending, but I want to\nspend the rest of all the seasons in\nthe company of my good, fair friends.)
(And with that wish in my heart,\nI take his outstretched hand...)
